      {
        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "Notes and context:\n- We searched the SRD‑46 stability database by IDs for Pu(IV) with acetylsalicylate (aspirin; ligand_8701) and, recognizing aspirin hydrolyzes in aqueous media, also for salicylate (ligand_9257). Both searches returned no measured stability constants. Broader Pu(IV) data exist in SRD‑46 (e.g., with nitrate, chloride, oxalate, acetylacetonate), but not with aspirin/salicylate.\n- Practical caveats: Aspirin readily hydrolyzes to salicylate in water, and Pu(IV) undergoes strong hydrolysis and can form colloids; these factors may limit published constants for this specific system.",
